oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Sam Steele
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Sam R. Steele, of Dickson, Tennessee, taking an inventory of his home food supply produced on his own farm (in this case 1180 pounds of meat). He is wearing eyeglasses with a jacket as he examines a piece of meat.
The Home Food Supply Program was a war-relief program instituted by the administration of Gov. Prentice Cooper.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
